[2
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 1998 16:19:53 -0700 (PDT)
From: Betty Blair <ai@artnet.net>

Re:
>[For the geographically challenged, Armenia & Azerbaijan share a common
border, and in fact a piece of Armenia, called Nogorno-Karabakh, is
entirely surrounded by Azerbaijani territory. - Mod.JW
Please note that Nagorno Karabakh is NOT part of Armenia though Armenians
live there... [and Nagorno-Karabakh wants to be independent from
Azerbaijan and has declared its independence.
Disease-bearing mosquitoes from Armenia and from Azerbaijan [including
Nagorno-Karabakh know no geographic boundaries. The problem is serious for
all concerned. Don't lose sight of that fact. It's critical to the whole
region. There are no boundaries for mosquitoes and both Azerbaijan and
Armenia need help in eradicating the problem.
--
Betty Blair
e-mail: ai@artnet.net
